    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="hero-rule"></div>
        <div class="hero-eyebrow">A patient&apos;s story through the operating model</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">The system<br>that <em>finally</em><br>met him.</h1>
        <p class="hero-strap">Sean is 46 and has a learning disability. He has an annual health check, a brother who supports him, and a system that has failed him quietly for two decades. The reasonable adjustments exist on paper. The kit at home is the first time they meet him in practice. <strong>This is the access story that cuts across every other journey.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-portrait-box">
        <div class="hero-portrait-circ">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/sean.png" alt="Sean">
        </div>
        <div class="hero-portrait-name">Sean</div>
        <div class="hero-portrait-role">Horizontal cohort patient<br>The access story</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

