        <div class="ribbon-label">Long-term optimisation</div>
        <div class="ribbon-substage">the access story sustained</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FRAMING -->
  <div class="framing">
    <div class="framing-grid">
      <div class="framing-tile">
        <div class="framing-tile-eyebrow">The access North Star</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-h">The adjustments are not a kindness. They are the system finally working.</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-body">Sean&apos;s cohort lives 19.5 years shorter than the rest of the population. Thirty-nine per cent of those deaths are judged avoidable. The reasonable-adjustment digital flag has existed for years. <strong>The home pathway is the first venue where the flag actually changes how the service runs.</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="framing-tile">
        <div class="framing-tile-eyebrow">Why this works for him</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-h">Easy-read materials. Support worker in the loop. A venue he is already comfortable in.</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-body">The clinic was never the right place for Sean. The waiting room is loud. The phlebotomist is a stranger. The leaflet is at reading age 14 when he reads at reading age 8. <strong>Move the venue and the friction goes with it. Everything else can finally work.</strong></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STAGES -->
  <div class="stages">

    <!-- STAGE 1 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-1">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">01</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Stratification — the cohort the system was failing on paper</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Sean is on the learning disability register. He has had his annual health check most years. The system knows he exists. The reasonable-adjustment digital flag has been on his record since the Accessible Information Standard became a legal duty in 2016. None of that has yet changed how a blood test happens for him. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="sean-s1"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Sean Story/sean-stage1.png" alt="Sean Stage 1" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">They have always known about me. The bit they have not known how to do is what to do about it.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Sean&apos;s brother</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">79.9% of people on the learning disability register had an annual health check (March 2025). The Reasonable Adjustment Digital Flag is a national NHS record flag. The Accessible Information Standard has been a legal requirement since 2016. The infrastructure to identify the cohort has existed for years.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Identify the cohort, file the flag, send the standard letter, run the standard appointment, record the DNA when it does not work, repeat next year.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Hannah, GP. The annual health check team. The learning disability liaison nurse. Sean&apos;s brother.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="crosslinks">
          <div class="crosslinks-label">Where this lives in the model</div>
          <div class="crosslinks-row">
            <span class="crosslinks-tag">Who</span>
            <a href="HomeTest Operating Model - Persona Sean.html" target="_blank">Sean persona</a>
            <span class="crosslinks-tag">Why</span>
            <a href="HomeTest Operating Model - Why.html" target="_blank">The case for adjustment</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STAGE 2 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-2">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">02</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Identification — outreach that actually reaches him</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">The home-test offer reaches Sean through his brother and his support worker, with easy-read materials at his reading level. The reasonable-adjustment flag triggers the alternative communication pathway. The offer is recognisable, the language fits, the consent conversation works. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="sean-s2"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Sean Story/sean-stage2.png" alt="Sean Stage 2" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">My brother explained it. The pictures helped. I knew what to do because someone had thought about how I would know.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Sean</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">Easy-read materials, accessible-format letters, support-worker engagement, and the alternative-route pathway designed into the platform from the start. The cohort identification triggers the cohort-appropriate communication.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Send the standard letter. Watch it not get read. Record another DNA. Update the report saying engagement is low. Cycle.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Sean&apos;s brother. The support worker. The learning disability liaison nurse. Easy-read template authors.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="crosslinks">
          <div class="crosslinks-label">Where this lives in the model</div>
          <div class="crosslinks-row">
            <span class="crosslinks-tag">How</span>
            <a href="HomeTest Operating Model - Operational.html" target="_blank">Lane 2 — adjusted initiation</a>
            <span class="crosslinks-tag">Status</span>
            <a href="HomeTest Operating Model - Status.html" target="_blank">Reasonable adjustment programme</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STAGE 3 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-3">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">03</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Diagnosis — the test that finally happens</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">The kit arrives at Sean&apos;s home. His brother and the support worker are with him. The instructions are accessible. The sample is taken. The result goes to Hannah, the practice, the annual-health-check record. The blood that has not been drawn for three years gets drawn for the first time in a setting Sean trusts. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="sean-s3"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Sean Story/sean-stage3.png" alt="Sean Stage 3" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">He sat at the kitchen table with his brother and the support worker. He did the test. He did not flinch. The whole thing took half an hour. We had been trying for years.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Hannah</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">The clinical pathway is unchanged. The clinical result is the same biochemical measurement. What changes is the venue, the support model, and the recognition that the patient&apos;s engagement profile is the design constraint, not the patient&apos;s problem.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Refer for sedated venepuncture. Wait for a slot. Sean does not attend. Cycle.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Sean. His brother. The support worker. The home-test kit supplier. Hannah holding the clinical pathway.</div>
          </div>
