    <div class="stage" id="stage-4">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">04</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Treatment — care that continues with the adjustments in place</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">The result triggers the same clinical conversation Hannah would have with any patient. Iron status, lifestyle, prescription. The difference is that the conversation also happens with Sean&apos;s brother and support worker in the loop, in the format Sean can engage with. The treatment is the same treatment. The wrap-around is different. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="sean-s4"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Sean Story/sean-stage4.png" alt="Sean Stage 4" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">Hannah talks to me and to my brother. The pictures help. The instructions for the tablets came in the picture version too.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Sean</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">The clinical treatment pathway is unchanged. The communication pathway is adapted to the patient&apos;s needs. Easy-read prescribing instructions, alternative-format letters, and the reasonable-adjustment flag staying live across handovers all combine to make the treatment actually take.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Hand over a printed leaflet at reading age 14. Watch the patient nod. Wonder later why the tablets are not being taken correctly.</div>
