      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Long-term optimisation — the access story sustained</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Sean stays in the cohort the system actually holds. The next test is on a calendar his support worker shares. The flags stay live. The materials are still easy-read. The 19.5-year mortality gap is the system&apos;s problem, not Sean&apos;s. Holding him properly is what closing that gap is made of. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="sean-s5"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Sean Story/sean-stage5.png" alt="Sean Stage 5" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">It is something we just do now. The kit, the test, the result. He knows what it is. We know what it is. The system finally knows what it is.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Sean&apos;s brother</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">39% of reviewed deaths of people with a learning disability were assessed as avoidable (LeDeR annual report 2023, published 2025). Holding the cohort in proper engagement is the system&apos;s response to that finding. The home pathway is one of the first venues where the response is structural rather than aspirational.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Build accessibility into the policy. Watch it not change the practice. Run the same annual cycle. Lose patients quietly. Repeat.</div>
